WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:01.700
The paper begins with a leaky confined aquifer and a constant-rate pumping test.

00:01.700 --> 00:03.750
Drawdown is recorded through time at observation wells.

00:03.750 --> 00:05.800
The Rapid City comparison uses five wells at reported distances from RC-5.

00:05.800 --> 00:07.850
The classical radial relation pairs radial flux with the drawdown gradient.

00:07.850 --> 00:09.900
The lagging formulation assigns a phase lag to the radial flux.

00:09.900 --> 00:11.950
A second phase lag is assigned to the drawdown gradient.

00:11.950 --> 00:14.000
Equal lags cancel; setting both lags to zero gives Classical Darcy.

00:14.000 --> 00:16.167
The field comparison reports early-time fit improvement and a bounded lag spread.

00:16.167 --> 00:18.733
The fitted lag remains diagnostic of the test and model context, not universal.
